<topic id="customizing_js">
  <title>Customizing Web Author Using JavaScript Code</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Customizing Web Author using JavaScript</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_czs_dgk_54b">To extend the client-side functionality provided by <ph keyref="webappProduct"/>, you can use
      the <xref keyref="jscript_api">JavaScript API</xref>. To load your JavaScript customization
      code, use one of the following methods:<ul id="ul_dzs_dgk_54b">
        <li id="li_ezs_dgk_54b" irina="irina"><xref
            href="customizing_plugins.dita#customizing_plugins/webapp_bundle_js_files_in_plugin"
            >Bundle JavaScript code with a Java <term>plugin</term></xref>.</li>
        <li id="li_fzs_dgk_54b" irina="irina"><xref
            href="customizing_frameworks.dita#customizing_frameworks/adding_javascript_code_to_a_framework"
            >Bundle the JavaScript code with a <term>framework</term></xref>.</li>
        <li id="li_gzs_dgk_54b" irina="irina">If you are using the <xref
            href="https://github.com/oxygenxml/web-author-component-integration" format="html"
            scope="external">Web Author Component Integration sample project</xref>, add the code in
          the following file: <filepath>src/main/webapp/app/plugin.js</filepath>.</li>
        <li id="li_hzs_dgk_54b" irina="irina"><b>[Not Recommended]</b> Create a file called <filepath>plugin.js</filepath> and copy it
          in the <filepath>app</filepath> folder of the <ph keyref="webappProduct"/>
          deployment.</li>
      </ul></p>
